Description:
Sense of style and space
Built in 2014, this contemporary 27sq family home offers three living areas and three bedrooms. Upon arrival at the front door you are greeted with an impressive entry with built in cabinetry and formal lounge area. The master bedroom is oversized and offers walk in robe and ensuite. To the rear of the property, the clever use of both sloped and flat ceilings to the living areas, gives an opulent style and a sense of extra space throughout. The galley kitchen comprises stone benchtops with waterfall edges and undermount sink. There is a double oven, 900mm gas cooktop and a butlers pantry with additional storage. The rumpus room overlooking the alfresco area is huge in size and really sets this home apart from others. Bedrooms two and three are generous in sized with both offering built in robes and ceiling fans. Finally there is a huge family bathroom with bath, shower, vanity and toilet with a third toilet located nearby. Climate is controlled throughout by reverse cycle ducted heating/cooling. Externally there is a double garage with remotes and roller door to the rear and direct access into the home. This home needs to be inspected to appreciate what is on offer!

Description:
Simply stylish quality
This 6 star energy efficient craftsman built home has been designed to truly compliment the block taking full advantage of the northerly sun with its abundance of glass whilst also maximising the natural ventilation throughout. Imagine curling up on the couch in the morning enjoying the warm sun in the winter but with the 900mm eave keeping the hot sun out during Summer! Upon arrival to the home, you are met with a modern facade with rooflines which soar up towards the sky and a unique blend of materials. You know you're in for something special! Step inside and the passage, with its stunning timber grain vinyl plank flooring takes you towards the rear of the home where you will find an oversized kitchen, meals and family area which offers expansive glass across the rear of the home creating a unique indoor outdoor feel. The kitchen is both stylish and functional with its 900mm dual fuel cooker, beautiful stone benchtops with waterfall edges cascading down to the floor and its abundance of cupboards and bench space. Cleverly hidden behind the wall is a large walk in pantry which also houses the fridge/freezer. From there you literally step outside to a stunning decked outdoor entertaining area, making it ideal for those who just love to entertain! There is even an outside toilet with basin for your guests! The family room comprises of a cleverly designed niche with built in cupboards for all your stereo needs. The home has three bedrooms plus a study, with the oversized master bedroom enjoying a walk in robe with double hanging and additional shelving and an ensuite with oversized shower. The other two bedrooms both have built in robes and easily accommodate queen sized beds. For those who need more storage off the double garage is an additional room which has been plumbed for hot and cold water, making it ideal for those who want an office from home including hairdressing. Every small detail has been well considered with this home to ensure your comfort including double glazed windows throughout, reverse cycle ducted air conditioning, solar hot water and 5 k/W solar electricity. This home is immaculately presented with too many features to mention but if you enjoy quality, then you need to inspect what this home has to offer.

Description:
Gorgeous Family Home
Gorgeous four bedroom weatherboard family home has been renovated throughout and offers outdoor entertaining areas with different zones to suit your family's way of living! Internally, this home offers two living areas separated by a stunning white kitchen with timber benchtops which offers stainless steel cooker, dishwasher and an abundance of storage. To the front of the home are three bedrooms with family bathroom with shower, vanity and toilet. To the rear of the home is the fourth bedroom with laundry which also encompasses bath with shower over and a second toilet, conveniently located off the pool area of the home. Even though at some point in time, an extension has been added to this home, it all ties seamlessly into the original home with stunning murray pine floorboards laid throughout. There is ducted heating throughout, reverse cycle split systems, solid fuel heater and solar electricity panels. From the dining room there is roofed courtyard zone perfect for a sitting area or the additional dining zone. Then off the family room is an larger outdoor entertaining space overlooking the inground heated pool complete with underwater lights! Externally there is a large 12m x 6m (approx.) colorbond shed with a double carport attached to the front all securely located behind double gates. This home is immaculately presented and will pleasantly surprise all those who take the time to inspect.

Description:
Quality Home In A Great Location
This excellent three bedroom, brick venner family home is located within close proximity to schools, Scotts oval, bushland and walking tracks.
Large kitchen area with wall oven, dishwasher and lots of bench space. Tiled meals area, ceiling fan, reverse cycle split system air conditioner, and sliding doors opening to the patio and side yard. Separate sunken lounge with solid fuel heater. All bedrooms offer built in robes, and the main with an ensuite. Ducted evaporative cooling throughout. Externally there is a covered patio/barbecue area, double carport, caravan/boat port and a lockup shed with concrete floor and power.
A great investment property with excellent tenants in place, or a fantastic first home. Inspection will not disappoint.

Description:
Mortgagee in Possession - Investors & First Home Buyers Take Note!
This solid brick veneer residence is sited on a generous 960 square metre block in a very convenient location close to shops and schools.
Features a spacious open living area with cathedral ceilings, timber floating floors, reverse cycle split system air conditioning and sliding doors opening onto the large 3m wide entertaining area. Appealing kitchen with a wall oven. Two generous bedrooms with built-in robes and ceiling fans. Bathroom with a spa and floor-to-ceiling tiles, plus a separate toilet and laundry.
Excellent car accommodation with a four vehicle lockup carport, another single carport, and a 9m x 6m lockup shed with concrete floor and power.
This property has loads of potential and is a must to inspect!

Description:
Greatly reduced in price by motivated vendor
This property has been greatly reduced in price as the vendor is very motivated for a quick sale. Set amid the back drop of the Murray River Bushland and backing onto the levee, this sophisticated residence has been architecturally designed with impressive proportions and an uplifting sense of tranquillity with all rooms enjoying seamless views of the captivating gardens and native backdrop. Offering three bedrooms plus study and three living areas this home really does have everything a growing family needs. Upon entry, the distinctive ceilings with celestial windows in the living areas add to the sense of spaciousness and a central feature brick wall with fireplace separates the large family/dining from the light filled living room. The third living space opens onto a private patio area as well as being open to the kitchen and separate meals areas. The impressive amount of glazing in the kitchen makes you feel like you are out in the garden preparing your meals. The enviable sized kitchen is equipped with cooktop, wall oven, dishwasher and impressive sized breakfast bar. Separating the living zones from the bedroom wing is a stunning glazed link that seamlessly expands this space onto the beautiful double courtyard and tranquil ferneries. This wing offers three comfortable bedrooms with an ensuite to the master. Opulent bathroom has spa set in a tiled podium complimented by oversized shower and vanity. Laundry offers additional storage and separate third toilet. Double garage with separate storage for workshop has direct access into the home for added security. Extra features include ducted reverse cycle heating/cooling, gas log fire place, solar panels, bore water, sprinklers throughout the lawns and gardens and much more.
